description: Beginning a new era for the Exiles — with a new team, and a new mandate to safeguard the fate and future of the Omniverse. New leader, new members, new worlds, new adversaries. They’ve barely begun to get to know one another when they’re thrust into their first mission — summoned to a world where the dawn of the historic Marvel Age turns out instead to be a prelude to global catastrophe. Meanwhile, back at the Crystal Palace, Sage struggles with a psychic curse that may well make her the new team’s greatest liability. Collecting NEW EXILES #1-6.
name: New Exiles: New Life, New Gambit

volume.name: New Exiles: New Life, New Gambit

description: It's the start of a new arc pitting the World's Greatest Detective and The Man of Steel against a shape-shifting villain! But why is this new baddie continuing a thousand-year-old war against Krypton? Featuring Art by Ardian Syaf and written by fan-favorite scribe Joe Casey!
name: The Big Noise - Part 1: Rumble Face

description: Sabretooth and Cat finish their face-off against Madame Hydra and her evil band of crosstime killers. Then, the Exiles deal with the fallout of their last two missions…oh, and that pesky impending End of All that Is, the death and destruction of the OmniVerse! Collecting NEW EXILES #13-15 and NEW EXILES ANNUAL #1.
name: Volume 3

description: As the New Exiles fight beside the Sons of Iron and Daughters of the Dragon to save their planet, a deadly force from the Exiles own past returns for a final showdown. Empress Hydra is back, and with her minions at her side only one thing is for certain: someone must die! Then, the heart wants what the heart wants and the sadistic Slaymaster wants Psylocke’s heart…literally! The Elizabeth Braddock of Earth-616 has slipped through his nefarious fingers one too many times, but he’s finally cornered her on a world targeted by Empress Hydra for extermination! Plus, Before she can come home to the X-Men, Betsy Braddock has one final mission—settle the score once and for all with the man who’s been hunting her across the multiverse. If she hopes to survive, Psylocke’s going to have to use every weapon at her disposal—and possibly cross a line no X-Man ever has before. Collecting NEW EXILES #16-18 and X-MEN: SWORD OF THE BRADDOCKS #1
name: Volume 4

description: One of the three one-shot issues (the other two are Bombast #1 and Captain Glory #1) from Jack Kirby's Secret City Saga. This issue focuses on Night Glider.
name: She Glides in Beauty Like the Night...

description: The hero from Pacific Comics, Morgan Miller returns as Silver Star in Topps Comics' Kirbyverse!
name: Odds Against Part 1: The Job

description: Captain Victory returns from Pacific Comics. Could this be the end of the Kirbyverse?!
name: Invasion

In the idyllic kingdom of Haven, the Frog Bombers are playing the Gobtown Crushers for the pennant, and the winner is…on trial for murder. The star player for the winning team has been accused of committing a capital crime during the drunken victory celebrations. So far, Flycatcher (a.k.a. King Ambrose) has managed to avoid spilling blood in the formation of his new kingdom. But now he has to judge a trial wherein the only penalty for the guilty is death. Featuring guest-artist David Lapham (YOUNG LIARS, SILVERFISH).
name: Out to the Ball Game, Part 1 of 2

"India" part 3 of 4. Meeta's dreams of Bollywood fame are threatened by a grotesque creature from the British Raj. It looks like the only person who can save her is John Constantine. But Constantine's got a surprise visitor: someone who might just turn his life around. With greed, sex, demons and dancing, Mumbai has never been hotter than this.
name: India, Part Three: No Dancing, No Singing.

description: Archie is determined to take Betty to the big dance, and he won't let little things like inclement weather, a car in need of repair and lack of funds get in the way! Then, when Reggie unleashes a practical joke spree, the teachers enlist the other students to fight... err.. prank back! Plus, other new and classic tales, puzzles, pin-ups, and more!

Based on the acclaimed bestselling psychological thriller from Dennis Lehane, timed to release with the feature film directed by Martin Scorsese and starring Leonardo DiCaprio. In 1954, U.S. Marshal Teddy Daniels and his partner, Chuck Aule, are sent to Shutter Island to find a mass murderer who has escaped from Ashcliffe Hospital, an institution for the criminally insane. Following a trail of puzzling clues, Daniels and Aule realize they've stumbled into an evil puzzle. But the closer they get to the truth, the more elusive it becomes, and the more they begin to fear that someone is trying to drive them insane.
name: Vol. 1

description: Kouichi and Mao are childhood best friends. But as they enter high school, they discover that they've been slowly drifting apart. They use to be really close friends during middle school but now at high school they rarely talk. They've become two very different people. Mao is a stunning girl, who has no problems attracting the opposite sex, while Kouichi...well...he could use a little help. And thus begins Mao's quest to make sure that even though Kouichi entered high school not having kissed a girl, he sure as hell won't graduate that way!
name: Vol. 1

description: When Koichi meets Asuka, it's love at first kick! Asuka is a soccer prodigy who needs help in her training to be the best. Jumping at the chance to hang out with this athletic beauty, Koichi quickly volunteers. But he soon finds himself pushed to the limit both physically and emotionally. Can these two score in the game of love? Sell Sheet Keynote: No young man should graduate high school without first getting kissed!
name: Vol. 2

description: It's a modern-day Princess and the Pauper, when Aihara meets sheltered little rich girl Mitsuki. When Aihara 'accidentally' locks lips with our latest heroine, will she forsake her familial responsibilities and open herself to the brave new world of love? Sell Sheet Keynote: No young man should graduate high school without first getting kissed!
name: Vol. 3

description: Collecting two pivotal storylines and a one-shot from acclaimed writer Garth Ennis. Reprinting HELLBLAZER #49 (featuring a very special Constantine Christmas), #52-55 ("Royal Blood," which pits Constantine against the demon Calibraxis), and #59-61 ("Guys and Dolls," which sets the stage for the final showdown between Constantine and the First of the Fallen).
name: TPB

description: Battling exhaustion and her prescription addiction, Blythe pulls Zayn into her history, revealing the mysterious way she came to be hired at Clearfleet Airlines. And in order to escape Blythe's past, Zayn must tell her a secret about her future – and hope that the woman he loves is stronger than the forces aligned against her.
name: The Picture of Blythe Alice Cameron

description: We meet Barton Aygrad, the burger Fool, as his store is demolished during the building of Utopia Park on Paris Island. We are introduced to Governor Samuel Winter and the Fantastegist, Utopia Park designer. The owners of Lucky Cola seek out the Blood Syndicate to be their new spokesmen. We see Mayor Jefferson get pressured to push Utopia through to completion. We see the change Utopia is bringing and the foreshadowing of violence to come.
name: Skeleton at the Feast

description:
In 1869, the life pod of an adult alien crashed in the cotton fields of the South. Discovered by a slave woman, the extraterrestrial's genetic structure was reconfigured and he was transformed into an African American baby. Now, over a hundred and twenty years later, Augustus Freeman is a successful lawyer who covertly uses his alien super-powers to help those in need. But when a teenaged girl from the streets convinces him to use his abilities to inspire his people, the affluent Augustus embraces his true destiny and becomes Icon, the hero of Dakota.

Presenting for the first time, Icon: A Hero's Welcome! This trade paperback collects the first 8 eight issues of Milestone Media's best selling comic.
name: TPB

description:
Since his first modern day appearance in Justice League of America, now get a look at Icon's first adventures from Milestone Media! Back again for the first time ever, this newprint collects the first eight issues! To quote Alan Moore, "ICON is that rarest of creatures - a well-told adventure story that achieves genuine political depth. Highly recommended."

Collects Icon 1-8.
name: TPB

description: Nightmare has claimed Earth. His unreal universe of pain and terror has been made tangible and spread across the globe by an army comprised of the world’s most powerful supernatural beings. Negating the sacrifice of a former Sorcerer Supreme, Jericho Drumm has opened the long-sealed gateway to Bondyè to ask the Voodoo Loa’s for aid. However, what he finds in the strange god land may very well shatter his world forever!

volume.name: Doctor Voodoo: Avenger of the Supernatural

description: Between the flak, the searchlights, the night fighters and the freezing, airless cold at twenty-thousand feet, bombing Germany in midwinter is no joke at all- but with some of the friends he's got, pilot Ken Harding might not even need any enemies. Ken gets to know his crew a little better, as they edge towards the last operation that will complete their tour of duty. One more nightmare flight, and then they can all go home...
name: 2: In Pomgolia
